==English==
===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] /'pætrɒnajz/

===Etymology===
From the {{L.}} ''[[pater]]'' meaning "father", with the -ize suffix used to create the verb form.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|patroniz|ing}}
# make a [[patron]]
# Treat as inferior unduly, talk down to, treat condescendingly.
# To make oneself a regular [[customer]] of a business.

====Translations====
